<subSubSection id="C359FCF8FFC8FFE9FF5498D9FB2E05B1" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BFCAF73FFC8FFE9FF5498D9FB2E05B1" blockId="2.[136,1452,1706,1984]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC8FFE9FF5498D9FF2804B5" bold="true" box="[136,210,1706,1732]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">Notes.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC8FFE9FF0B98D9FD9204B5" authority="Rose (1905: 301)" authorityName="Rose" authorityPageNumber="301" authorityYear="1905" box="[215,616,1706,1733]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="holwayana">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC8FFE9FF0B98D9FE5E04B5" box="[215,420,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">Cassia holwayana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC8FFE9FE7598D9FD9204B5" author="Rose, J. N." box="[425,616,1706,1733]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" pagination="281 - 339" refId="ref5830" refString="Rose, J. N. (1905) Studies of Mexican and Central American plants - No. 4. In: Cook, R &amp; Maxon, C. (Eds.) Contributions from the United States National Herbarium, v. 8, n. 4. Government printing office, Washington, pp. 281 - 339. [https: // www. jstor. org / stable / 23490910]" type="book chapter" year="1905">Rose (1905: 301)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is a new name for 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC8FFE9FCEF98D9FB0F04B5" authority="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" authorityName="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" authorityYear="1843" box="[819,1269,1706,1732]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflora">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC8FFE9FCEF98D9FC0E04B5" box="[819,1012,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">Cassia multiflora</emphasis>
M. Martens &amp; Galeotti
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC8FFE9FAC998D9FF440499" author="Hayez, M." pageId="2" pageNumber="188" refId="ref5140" refString="Hayez, M. (1843) Bulletins de l'Academie royale des sciences, des lettres et des beaux-arts de Belgiqu e, t. X, p. II. L'Academie royale, Bruxelles, 582 pp." type="book" year="1843">Hayez (1843: 307)</bibRefCitation>
, which was described based on the collection 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC8FFE9FD0F98BCFC660499" box="[723,924,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">H. Galleotti 3145</emphasis>
. It is an illegitimate name, however, as 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC8FFE9FAB798BDFF05057D" author="Vogel, T." pageId="2" pageNumber="188" refId="ref6220" refString="Vogel, T. (1837) Synopsis Generis Cassiae. Typis Nietackianis, Berlin, 79 pp." type="book" year="1837">Vogel (1837: 39)</bibRefCitation>
previously described a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC8FFE9FD509881FD22057D" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[652,728,1778,1804]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC8FFE9FD509881FD22057D" box="[652,728,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">Cassia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the same epithet (homonymous). Additionally, the 
<taxonomicName id="4C43D4F0FFC8FFE9FA839881FF020541" authorityName="M. Martens &amp; Galeotti" authorityYear="1843" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Cassia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multiflora">
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC8FFE9FA839881FF020541" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">Cassia multiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
protologue does not indicate in which herbarium the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFC8FFE9FC969965FC560541" box="[842,940,1814,1840]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">holotype</typeStatus>
was deposited. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC8FFE9FB819965FA5D0540" author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[1117,1447,1814,1841]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" pagination="1 - 454" refId="ref5268" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 454." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby (1982: 560)</bibRefCitation>
, when performing the new combination, mistakenly indicated the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFC8FFE9FCB99949FC3D0525" box="[869,967,1850,1876]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">holotype</typeStatus>
deposited at the Brussels Herbarium (BR), which 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC8FFE9FF0E992DFE5B0508" author="Prado, J. &amp; Hirai, R. Y. &amp; Moran, R. C." box="[210,417,1886,1913]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" pagination="651 - 651" refId="ref5617" refString="Prado, J., Hirai, R. Y. &amp; Moran, R. C. (2015) (046 - 048) Proposals concerning inadvertent lectotypifications (and neotypifications). Taxon 64: 651 - 651. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / 643.29" type="journal article" year="2015">
Prado 
<emphasis id="B9377361FFC8FFE9FEC6992CFEAB0509" box="[282,337,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">et al.</emphasis>
(2015)
</bibRefCitation>
called an inadvertent lectotypification. Therefore, we are designating the specimen deposited at BR, under barcode 000000521559 as the 
<typeStatus id="54F811D1FFC8FFE9FDB799F1FD2F05ED" box="[619,725,1922,1948]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188">lectotype</typeStatus>
, as it is the most complete specimen, with leaves and flowers, and is well preserved; additionally, the main collections of Galeotti are deposited in BR (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD2D282FFC8FFE9FBE799D5FB3D05B1" author="Thiers, B." box="[1083,1223,1958,1984]" pageId="2" pageNumber="188" refId="ref6117" refString="Thiers, B. (2021) Index Herbariorum: a global directory of public herbaria and associated staff. New York Botanical Garden's Virtual Herbarium, New York. Available from: http: // sweetgum. nybg. org / ih / (accessed 25 July 2021)." type="url" year="2021">Thiers 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
